The paper focuses on a visualization recommender system for exploratory data analysis, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and database (DB) technologies. The system uses ranking metrics to identify guideposts for visualizations, which relates to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of visualization in data exploration, which falls under the category of visualization (VIS) in computer science.
